      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Addition of HBr to a double bond with an ether (−OR) substituent occurs regiospecifically to give a product in which the −Br and −OR are bonded to the same carbon. Draw the two possible carbocation intermediates in this electrophilic addition reaction, and explain using resonance why the observed product is formed.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbEFUIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b42b5659f2c1e2796229d1767e34ad82c1c4fdf7/OChem_10_EC_033.jpg\" alt=\"1-methoxycyclohexene reacts with hydrogen bromide to form 1-bromo-1-methoxycyclohexane.\">",
